{
  "description": "A vibrant ruby-throated hummingbird perches delicately on a thin, curving branch. The bird is viewed from behind, showcasing its iridescent green back and a striking ruby-red throat patch (gorget). Its long, slender beak points slightly upwards. The background is a soft, blurred wash of green foliage, creating a bokeh effect with patches of bright sunlight filtering through the leaves. The branch itself is a dark brown, providing a contrast to the bird's bright colors and the green backdrop.",
